default, but can be customized by implementing RotatePolicy interface\n- DateRotatePolicy available as an alternative rotation implementation, configured via rotatePolicy and rotateTime settings\n- Custom LogWriter extensions created by implementing the LogWriter interface or extending LogWriterSupport for formatter support\n- Custom LogFormatter implementations use the LogFormatter interface with LogLevelLabelProvider for customizable log level labels\n- Placeholders added by creating LogItem implementations and extending BasicLogFormatter to override getLogItems\n- Initialization messages suppressed by copying the base writer class source, removing the initialization log output, and overriding needsToWrite to filter out \"initialized.\" messages before setting the custom class in log.properties\n- log_adaptor doesn't output initialization messages so no suppression needed there\n\nKnowledge file s5 covers all of this. ✓\n\nLooking at the source more carefully, I see the initialization suppression involves removing the output from the initializeWriter() method and then using needsToWrite to prevent those messages from appearing in the logs. The knowledge file has the right approach but doesn't show the specific code example - though that's fine since it's just demonstrating what gets deleted rather than new implementation details. I'm verifying the remaining sections against the source material. The FileLogWriter rotation behavior, LogWriter and LogFormatter configurations, and the options argument all check out correctly against what's documented.\n\nNow I'm double-checking the init message suppression section more carefully. The knowledge file describes overriding `needsToWrite` in LogWriterSupport to suppress the initialization message starting with \"initialized.\" on the first call, and the source material confirms this approach with the same method override pattern. ソースコードの例では、BufferedOutputStreamを初期化する際に削除すべき初期化メッセージの出力処理が示されている。知識ファイルではこのコード例は省略されているが、削除対象の